I"p<h3 id="simple">Simple</h3>

<p>No more databases, comment moderation, or pesky updates to install—just <em>your content</em>.</p>

<h3 id="static">Static</h3>

<p><a href="https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/">Markdown</a>, <a href="https://github.com/Shopify/liquid/wiki">Liquid</a>, HTML &amp; CSS go in. Static sites come out ready for deployment.</p>

<h3 id="blog-aware">Blog-aware</h3>

<p>Permalinks, categories, pages, posts, and custom layouts are all first-class citizens here.</p>

<h3 id="free-hosting-with-github-pages">Free hosting with GitHub Pages</h3>

<p>Sick of dealing with hosting companies? <a href="https://pages.github.com/">GitHub Pages</a> are <em>powered by Jekyll</em>, so you can easily deploy your site using GitHub for free—<a href="https://help.github.com/articles/about-supported-custom-domains/">custom domain name</a> and all.</p>
